  <TITLE>Change Email Address Template in Email Auth with PKCE flow for SSR needs to be corrected</TITLE>
  <DESCRIPTION>There is nice documentation on how to configure a Supabase project to handle email authentication in a server-side rendered (SSR) application. But, I think the example template for the `Change Email Address` case is incorrect [Link](https://github.com/supabase/supabase/blob/02dd1b643a94f549f1014bb18bd2db8b643268db/apps/docs/pages/guides/auth/server-side/email-based-auth-with-pkce-flow-for-ssr.mdx#L235C12-L235C12) Instead of ``` &lt;h2&gt;Confirm Change of Email&lt;/h2&gt; &lt;p&gt;Follow this link to confirm the update of your email from {{ .Email }} to {{ .NewEmail }}:&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;{{ .ConfirmationURL }}&quot;&gt;Change Email&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt; ``` It should follow the pattern of the other templates and be ``` &lt;h2&gt;Confirm Change of Email&lt;/h2&gt; &lt;p&gt;Follow this link to confirm the update of your email from {{ .Email }} to {{ .NewEmail }}:&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;{{ .SiteURL }}/api/store/auth/confirm?token_hash={{ .TokenHash }}&amp;type=email_change&quot;&gt;Change Email&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt; ``` This should be an easy change. I am happy to make a PR if you want.</DESCRIPTION>
